issue.title: Search cm
issue.body:
* **The Name of this branch is**
search-cm

* **Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements**
- [ ] All files contain comments including Author, Purpose
- [ ] All methods contain comments including Purpose, And Argument List and a short purpose for each argument
- [ ] Tests for the changes have been added (for bug fixes / features)
- [ ] Docs have been added / updated (for bug fixes / features)



* **What kind of change does this PR introduce?** (Bug Fix, Feature, Document Update...)
FEATURE - search products by title or delivery location


* **What Ticket is associated with this PR**
#4 + #5 


* **What is the new behavior?**  (if this is a feature change)

When a user is logged in they are presented with search functionality in the nav bar - they can select either product or local delivery as search options, enter a string into the text filed, and when the search button is pressed - they will be presented with a list of products that matches the input.

* **List all core functionality** (Must include at least one Unit Test for Each)
Search products by a user inputted string by the product title or the product localdevlivery properties

* **Other information / Steps to Test**:
git fetch
git checkout search-cm
run!
log into the application
add 2 products into the system via the sell a product tab in the nav bar
Call the first product pants and do not include a local delivery location
call the second product something different and use pants as the local delivery location
navigate back to the home page
use the search bar to search for pants with the product selected in the select box
the first product you entered should be returned
search for pants again with local delivery selected in the select box
the second object should be returned
